Mobile Creches
January 7 ·
Mobile Creches
December 21, 2018 ·

Mobile Creches was invited to speak at the Early Childhood Development panel organized as a part of National CSR Summit; Re-Imagining CSR: Innovate. Integrate. Impact. conducted by CII (Confederation of Indian Industry) held on 18th Dec at ITC Maurya.

Sumitra Mishra [Executive Director- Mobile Creches] shared the panel with Ms. Ms. Sunisha Ahuja [Early Childhood Education Specialist, UNICEF India], Ms. Uma Mahadevan [Principal Secretary- Women & Child Development; Empowerment... of differently abled and Senior Citizens Departments, Government of Karnataka], Ms. Nisha Singh [Advisor- Deputy Chief Minister of Delhi].

The discussion was moderated by Ms. Leena Prakash [Founder- Mission Anganwadi & expert in early childhood development]. Panelists responded to pertinent questions around need for investing in early years, why convergence with government and industry is the key to scaling up accessible and inclusive #earlychildhoodcareandeducation services, and how CSR partnerships can support long term quality services for young children.

#earlychildhooddevelopement #ECCD #childcareservices #convergence

Mobile Creches
December 12, 2018 ·

Mobile Creches was invited by Toxics Link to the Environment Film Festival- Quotes from the Earth, 2018 on 7th December. 10 children from Rajabazar daycare centre participated in the inaugural ceremony. The 5 to 6 years old children performed on a tik tok-tik tok song that urged adults to urgently stop using plastic and save the environment for their future generations. The performance was loved by everyone. Mr. Ravi Aggarwal, executive director, Toxic Link, appreciated the little ones with cute bags and certificates.

Thanks to Rahul Chauniyal from Infinity Danspiration Studio for training the little ones...

#quotesfromtheearth2018 #mobilecreches #childrenurgeadults #careforenvironment #earlychildhoodcareanddevelopment

Mobile Creches
December 4, 2018 ·

On 2nd Dec 2018, @Mobile Creches hosted its exclusive 50th year fund raiser – the soul stirring - Dastan E-Karn, by Mahmood Farooqui. More than 200 guests were mesmerized by his performance. It was a special occasion when many old and new friends and supporters of Mobile Creches came together to celebrate our long journey in providing quality #earlychildhoodcareanddevelopment to thousands of young children from the most vulnerable communities across India.

Devika Singh, (C...o-founder of Mobile Creches) said, “The powerful performance- Dastan E-Karn, in the beautiful setting of Anandagram, amidst a host of fellow travelers and supporters, was deeply moving. It was a fitting tribute to the spirit of Meera Mahadevan, who took the fearless step of raising her voice for countless young children in our country, encouraging a fightback and constructive work against injustice and neglect, forcing open doors of opportunity for every child. Karna’s bitter hurt, must keep ringing in our ears. For all of you who put this event together and made it possible, appreciation and gratitude”

Thank you PNB Housing Finance Ltd., Sanskriti Kendra, Hero Motocorp Ltd., Rambagh Palace Hotels, HCL Corporation Ltd. and so many supporters who helped us put together this outstanding event.

#children #MC@50 #earlychildhoodcareanddevelopment #nurturingcare #RighttoECD
